700842f-a.title: Bronx: Cypress Avenue - 133rd Street (East)
700842f-a.text:
108 to 88 Cypress Ave., at, adjoining and south of the S.E. corner of
East 133rd Street. The 1-story brick structures are garages.
April 12, 1931.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.

700030f-a.title: Bronx: 133rd Street (East) - Cypress Avenue
700030f-a.text:
East 133rd Street, east from Cypress Ave. In the background is
the United Electric Light and Power Co. plant on the East River Shore.
April 12, 1931.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.

700843f-a.title: Bronx: Cypress Avenue - 133rd Street
700843f-a.text:
114 to 120 Cypress Ave., adjoining and north of the N.E. corner of
East 133rd Street. The corner was occupied by No. 112, another 3-story
frame house.
April 12, 1931.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.
